This paper deals with multi-class classification, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper proposes algorithms for finding the Bayes-optimal prediction, which is a fundamental problem in statistical decision theory. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
